Tell me about Cash ISAs.
A Cash ISA is a type of savings account that allows you to deposit money and earn tax-free interest.  The main difference between a regular savings account and a Cash ISA is that the interest you earn is tax-free. This can help your savings grow faster.  You can pay up to £20,000 into a combination of permitted ISAs this tax year.  Cash ISAs cannot be joint accounts.  You can withdraw money, but it depends on the terms of your account. Some, like an Instant Access Cash ISA, let you withdraw at any time.  However, withdrawals from fixed-term accounts may incur charges or fees, or even void the agreement. Always check your terms and conditions before withdrawing.  Reputable Cash ISAs are protected by the Financial Services Compensation Scheme (FSCS) up to £85,000 per person, per provider.
